latestPosts.caption:
Some tattoos are memories..some tattoos are self expression..some help us heal..some are pure art!! 

As time changes, we evolve…we may sometimes want to part with some old memories! 

With Q switch Ndyag technology we can achieve to erase the tattoos you no longer relate with .. let me clear some common doubts

Is it painful ?
With good numbing cream, quite bearable

How many sessions are needed?
Depends on the tattoo .. professional tattoo needs more number of sessions 7-8..whereas amateur tattoos need less

Can all colours get targeted?
Only black n blue ink gets targeted well.

What should be the ideal gap between sessions?
It’s ideal to give 2 months gap between sessions. Longer the gap, tattoo keeps getting lighter

Is there any side effect?
Well, if not done with good acumen or proper understanding of the technology, one can see scarring. Tattoo granulomas are not uncommon.

So, Choose a qualified dermatologist with good laser technology , get a proper consultation and do not refrain from clearing all your doubts before diving into the procedure.
